snippet: Hannah Graham, the missing University of Virginia student whose remains were discovered Oct. 18, was a victim of a homicide, the Albemarle County Police Department said Tuesday.
abstract: Authorities in Virginia conclude that case of missing University of Virginia student Hannah Graham, whose remains were later discovered, is a homicide; Jesse L Matthew Jr has been charged with her abduction with intent to defile.
lead_paragraph: Hannah Graham, the missing University of Virginia student whose remains were discovered Oct. 18, was a victim of a homicide, the Albemarle County Police Department said Tuesday.

headline.main: Virginia: College Student’s Death Was a Homicide, Police Say
headline.print_headline: Virginia: College Student’s Death Was a Homicide, Police Say
